snippet.title: Johnny Depp Feels ‘Boycotted’ In Hollywood After Amber Heard Drama
snippet.description:
Johnny Depp says he feels like he is being boycotted in Hollywood, following his legal battle with ex-wife Amber Heard. The “Pirates of the Caribbean” actor opened up to The Sunday Times in a new interview, which focuses on his latest film, “Minamata.” In the interview, Johnny got candid about his status in Hollywood. “Some films touch people and this affects those in ‘Minamata’ and people who experience similar things. And for anything … for Hollywood’s boycott of me? One man, one actor in an unpleasant and messy situation, over the last number of years,” he said.
